"'''Only Droids Serve the Maker'''" is a short story written by [[Kathy Tyers]] with illustrations by [[Matt Busch]] and [[Mike Vilardi]]. It was published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 10|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' ''10'']] in [[May]] [[1996]] by [[West End Games]] before being made available online at [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]] on [[January 11]], [[2007]].

It is the third installment in the series of short stories involving [[Tinian I'att Azur-Jamin|Tinian I'att]] and [[Daye Azur-Jamin]].

==Plot summary==
After the attack on [[Silver Station]] that cut off his [[Bacta tank/Legends|bacta treatment]] [[Daye Azur-Jamin]]—now reliant on [[Cybernetics/Legends|cybernetics]]—joins [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] gunrunners [[Woyiq]] and [[Toalar Yalom Yalom|Toalar]]. While on a mission to [[Monor II]], the trio is intercepted by an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Starship/Legends|vessel]] as they attempt to drop a [[message pod]] to the [[Sunesi]] resistance, revealing the location of a hidden [[Weapon/Legends|weapons]] cache.

Under the command of the new Imperial administrator [[Brago]], who wishes to deal with the Sunesi and their allies by force, [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Karr]] takes the trio into [[Prison/Legends|custody]] for [[Death/Legends|termination]]. In his cell, two [[Stormtrooper/Legends|troopers]] start dismantling Azur-Jamin's cybernetics, leaving him blinded and crippled.

The captives are later rescued by Rebel [[Spy/Legends|spy]] [[Urek]], along with two Sunesi [[Agent/Legends|operatives]] and a [[Protocol droid/Legends|protocol droid]]. One of the Sunesi, [[Nee]], shows Azur-Jamin how to heal himself using the [[The Force/Legends|Force]], enabling him to restore his sight. They are then taken to the Sunesi's [[City/Legends|village]].

Meanwhile, [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] [[Tinian I'att Azur-Jamin|Tinian I'att]] and [[Chenlambec]] tracked down [[Agapos the Ninth|Agapos IX]], the Sunesi leader on whom the Imperials have placed a [[Death mark/Legends|death mark]]. They locate him in a hidden bunker and capture him after stunning his guards.

Although the Sunesi initially want to pursue the two bounty hunters, Azur-Jamin recognizes their ship and convinces the Sunesi to stand down - he suspects the two may be working undercover for the Rebellion. His intuition is correct: Chenlambec helps the Rebellion as a bounty hunter by faking the deaths of Rebel leaders and getting them out of the Imperial eye. He then presents "proof" of his kill in the form of [[Cloning/Legends|cloned]] tissue and claims their [[Bounty/Legends|bounty]].

Azur-Jamin follows the bounty hunters to [[Tekra Point|Tekra Station]], where he reunites with Agapos.

